    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm looking at this new high protein dog food for my lab, he's getting up there in age (around 9) and i wanna make sure i'm getting the macros right. what's a good protein to fat ratio for an older lab so he keeps his muscle but doesn't get too heavy?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For an older lab, you want a balance that supports muscle maintenance without causing too much weight gain. A good starting point for a protein to fat ratio is somewhere around 30-35% protein and 20-25% fat. It's important to remember that the *type* of protein matters, and you want something highly digestible, like a good quality, easily absorbed source. If you use a protein that's too dense, it's just as bad as a poorly constructed, overly-heavy-looking, but ultimately useless, bag of kibble.",
      "source": "target",
